e look. \n\nRemember, as a rectangle body type, you can pull off a variety of styles, so don\'t be afraid to experiment and find what works best for you!\n\n? **Personalized Styling Tips**:\n? **Personalized for abcd:**\n**As a Male:** Focus on fit and tailoring for a polished appearance\n**For your rectangle body type:** Add definition with belts or cinched waists to create curves\n**For your fair skin tone:** Pastels and soft colors complement fair skin beautifully',118,NULL,'2026-01-18 14:22:57'),(9,'938cf23e-cfcd-460b-93ce-96c52b03b28f',NULL,'user','my body shape?',0,NULL,'2026-01-18 14:23:39'),(10,'938cf23e-cfcd-460b-93ce-96c52b03b28f',NULL,'assistant','You have a rectangle body type. As a rectangle, you have a similar measurement around your bust, waist, and hips, which creates a straight up and down silhouette. This body type is often considered versatile and can pull off a wide range of styles. \n\nHere are some styling tips for your body type:\n\n1. Balance your silhouette with clothes that create curves, such as flared pants or A-line dresses.\n2. Emphasize your waist with belted dresses or tops to create a more defined silhouette.\n3. Highlight your assets with statement pieces, such as a bold necklace or a patterned scarf.\n4. Try asymmetrical necklines or hemlines to add visual interest to your outfit.\n5. Don\'t be afraid to experiment with different styles and find what works best for you!\n\nRemember, these are just general guidelines, and the most important thing is to wear what makes you feel confident and comfortable.',150,NULL,'2026-01-18 14:23:44'),(11,'938cf23e-cfcd-460b-93ce-96c52b03b28f',NULL,'user','my hair type?',0,NULL,'2026-01-18 14:23:58'),(12,'938cf23e-cfcd-460b-93ce-96c52b03b28f',NULL,'assistant','Your hair type is Straight, Wavy, Curly. \n\nHere are some styling tips for your hair type:\n\n1. For straight hair: Use a lightweight hair serum or oil to add shine and protect your hair from heat damage. You can also try a sleek and straight hairstyle with a center parting.\n2. For wavy hair: Use a texturizing spray or dry shampoo to add volume and texture to your hair. You can also try a beachy waves hairstyle with a bit of messy texture.\n3. For curly hair: Use a moisturizing shampoo and conditioner to keep your curls hydrated and defined. You can also try a curl-defining cream or gel to enhance your natural texture.\n\nRemember, these are just general guidelines, and the most important thing is to find a hairstyle that makes you feel confident and comfortable.\n\nHere is an outfit based on your profile: \nYou have straight, wavy, and curly hair types. This means you have a versatile hair texture that can be styled in many different ways. \n\nHere are some tips for styling your hair:\n\n1. For straight hair, try using a light hold styling product to add texture and prevent frizz.\n2. For wavy hair, use a sea salt spray or a texturizing spray to enhance natural texture and add volume.\n3. For curly hair, use a curl-defining cream or a curl-enhancing mousse to moisturize and define curls.\n\nRemember to use a wide-tooth comb or a detangling brush to gently detangle your hair, especially when it\'s wet. And don\'t forget to use a heat protectant spray when using heat styling tools to prevent damage.',267,NULL,'2026-01-18 14:24:04'),(13,'938cf23e-cfcd-460b-93ce-96c52b03b28f',NULL,'user','my hair type?\n\n',0,NULL,'2026-01-18 15:06:45'),(14,'938cf23e-cfcd-460b-93ce-96c52b03b28f',NULL,'assistant','You have straight, wavy, and curly hair types.',8,NULL,'2026-01-18 15:06:46'),(15,'938cf23e-cfcd-460b-93ce-96c52b03b28f',NULL,'user','my hair type',0,NULL,'2026-01-18 15:07:08'),(16,'938cf23e-cfcd-460b-93ce-96c52b03b28f',NULL,'assistant','Your hair type is straight, wavy, and curly.',8,NULL,'2026-01-18 15:07:09'),(17,'5b057aef-0407-4889-88de-f9145f929b3b',13,'user','tell me my details like measurements, body type, skin colour, hair type ect',0,NULL,'2026-01-18 15:15:49'),(18,'5b057aef-0407-4889-88de-f9145f929b3b